ADRS = [
("0001-rust-first.md","Rust-first trusted core","Accepted","A browser processes hostile inputs continuously; memory safety and explicit ownership reduce avoidable defect classes, while some mature native foundations remain necessary.","Use stable Rust for new trusted engine, broker, network-policy, storage-policy, IPC, and agent-policy code. Permit unsafe code and C ABI boundaries only in isolated crates with a written safety contract, fuzz targets, and named owner.","The project accepts a smaller browser-specific ecosystem and invests in FFI discipline, profiling, and compiler/toolchain qualification."),
("0002-multiprocess.md","Capability-bounded multi-process architecture","Accepted","A single-process design cannot provide credible containment for renderers, decoders, GPU drivers, storage, network protocol state, and AI tools.","Use separate UI, browser broker, renderer, network, storage, GPU, utility, and agent roles. Every channel is typed and every transferred resource is authorized by a broker.","Baseline memory is higher than a toy single process, so adaptive pools and lifecycle reclamation must optimize without weakening site isolation."),
("0003-independent-engine.md","Independent engine boundary","Accepted","The goal is architectural independence from Chromium, Gecko, and WebKit, not reinvention of every security-sensitive foundation.","Do not embed or fork an existing browser engine. Own DOM, style, layout, paint, navigation policy, process orchestration, product UI, and agent policy. Adopt audited cryptography, Unicode data, shaping, compression, codecs, and OS sandbox APIs through narrow interfaces.","Independence remains meaningful while avoiding custom cryptography and decades of duplicate standards work below the browser layer."),
("0004-ai-capability-security.md","Deterministic AI capability mediation","Accepted","Model outputs and page content are untrusted and prompt injection cannot be solved by prompting alone.","The model may observe sanitized context and propose structured actions, but a non-model policy engine validates origin, profile, document version, action class, expiry, user intent, confirmation, taint, and egress before execution.","Some convenient autonomous workflows require more confirmations; safety remains testable even when models change."),
("0005-memory-policy.md","Isolation-preserving memory reporting","Accepted","Browser memory comparisons are easy to game through process sharing, tab discard, hidden reloads, or different page sets.","Optimize browser-owned overhead with lifecycle states and same-site economics, but publish isolation mode, page corpus, discarded/frozen tabs, restore correctness, latency, and measurement APIs with every result.","Claims may look less dramatic, but remain credible and reproducible."),
("0006-license.md","MPL-2.0 bootstrap license","Accepted","The research engine should remain improvable in downstream products while allowing broader applications to combine it with differently licensed code.","License original bootstrap source under MPL-2.0, require Developer Certificate of Origin sign-off initially, and review third-party compatibility before adding dependencies.","File-level copyleft requires contributors and distributors to understand modification obligations; legal review is still required before commercial distribution."),
]

